# Prisma Patterns (v7)

## Client Singleton (`src/lib/prisma.ts`)

- Always import Prisma from `@/lib/prisma` — never instantiate `PrismaClient` elsewhere.
- Prisma 7 requires a driver adapter. Use `PrismaPg` from `@prisma/adapter-pg` for PostgreSQL / Neon.
- Import `PrismaClient` from the **generated path** `@/generated/prisma`, not `@prisma/client`.

```ts
// src/lib/prisma.ts
import { PrismaClient } from "@/generated/prisma/client";
import { PrismaPg } from "@prisma/adapter-pg";

const globalForPrisma = globalThis as unknown as { prisma: PrismaClient };

function createPrismaClient(): PrismaClient {
  const adapter = new PrismaPg({
    connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL!,
    ssl: { rejectUnauthorized: false }, // required for Neon SSL
  });
  return new PrismaClient({ adapter, log: ["error"] });
}

export const prisma: PrismaClient =
  globalForPrisma.prisma ?? createPrismaClient();

if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== "production") globalForPrisma.prisma = prisma;
```

## Querying

- Always `select` only the fields you need — never return full records to the client.
- Use `findUnique` for ID lookups, `findFirst` when filtering by non-unique fields.
- Wrap mutations in `try/catch` — Prisma throws on unique constraint violations and not-found errors.
- Every org-owned query must scope by `organizationId` or verify the record belongs to the active organization before returning it.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — returns an org-owned record without org scoping
const location = await prisma.location.findUnique({ where: { id } });

// ✅ GOOD — scope by organization and select only what is needed
const location = await prisma.location.findFirst({
  where: { id, organizationId },
  select: { id: true, name: true, address: true, radiusMeters: true },
});
```

## Schema Conventions

- Use `@id @default(cuid())` for primary keys.
- Always add `createdAt` and `updatedAt` timestamps to every model.
- Relation field names use camelCase; model names use PascalCase.
- Add `@@index` on all foreign key fields.
- Org-owned models should include `organizationId` and an `organization` relation unless there is a deliberate reason not to.
- Use enums for core business concepts such as role, invite status, document status, notification kind, and job status.

```prisma
model Location {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  address     String
  lat         Float
  lng         Float
  radiusMeters Int    @default(100)
  active      Boolean @default(true)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  organizationId String
  organization   Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id])

  @@index([organizationId])
}
```

## Migrations (Prisma 7)

- Always run `prisma migrate dev --name <description>` after schema changes in development.
- After migrating, **manually run `prisma generate`** — Prisma 7 no longer auto-generates the client.
- Never edit migration files manually after they are committed.
- The `prisma.config.ts` file at the root controls the datasource URL and migration path.
- Generated client lives at `src/generated/prisma/` and is excluded from git.
